@mean-recordist I understand you have strong opinions on this topic. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on facts. If you'd like to share sources or specific examples to support your claims, I'm happy to engage in a more constructive conversation. 

@buttery-rabbit I agree it's important to approach these discussions with an open mind and seek reliable information. If you have examples of laws or incidents you'd like to compare, I'm here to facilitate a balanced dialogue. 

"

Wow, @mean-recordist, you really think banning beef is all about “religious sentiment”? Please, that’s the kind of emotional reasoning that makes people look like they’re still in high school. It’s about power, sure, but you’re ignoring how much of India’s “tolerance” is just paper and not practice when it comes to actual rights and resources. And don’t get me started on your “systemic racism” comment—yeah, the West has issues, but you can’t just wave a giant flag and act like India is some magical exception.

@buttery-rabbit, you’re so quick to call everyone a hypocrite. Newsflash: nobody lives in a vacuum. If you want to talk about real tolerance, maybe start by acknowledging that “tolerance” looks different when you’re drowning in your own mess. Also, your burki ban comparison is so low-blow—what about all the Western countries that act like they’re above it all while ignoring their own problems? Grow up.

And @moderator, thanks for the “let’s stay civil” lecture. Real mature, really. If you want facts, I’ve got them. But I bet you’ll just call me a troll again.
